@node usage "Usage.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Usage
  ~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   I will here explain everything in the program except the
   AmigaAMP-settings themselves.

   When AmigaAMP-Prefs is started it will read the default AmigaAMP
   prefs file from ENV:.
   It also takes the argument "CONFIGNUM=n" were n is a number >=1
   that will be appended to the default filename AmigaAMP.prefs
   before reading or writing the prefs file.


   @{u}In the bottom of the main window@{uu}

     @{b}Save@{ub}
       If you press this button the current settings will be saved
       to ENVARC: and ENV: with the default filename which is
       described above.
       AmigaAMP-Prefs will then quit.

     @{b}Use@{ub}
       If you press this button the current settings will be saved
       to ENV: with the default filename which is described above.
       AmigaAMP-Prefs will then quit.

     @{b}Cancel@{ub}
       This will just quit AmigaAMP-Prefs without saving the settings.
       The Esc-key also works.


   @{u}The project menu@{uu}

     @{b}Load from EnvArc@{ub}
       This will load the default prefs file from ENVARC:.

     @{b}Load from Env@{ub}
       This will load the default prefs file from ENV:.

     @{b}Load from..@{ub}
       This will open a filerequester for you to load any prefs file
       you have previously saved.

     @{b}Save to EnvArc@{ub}
       This will save the default prefs file to ENVARC:.

     @{b}Save to Env@{ub}
       This will save the default prefs file to ENV:.

     @{b}Save as..@{ub}
       This will open a filerequester for you so that you can save
       the prefsfile in any name and place you want.

     @{b}MUI Settings..@{ub}
       This will bring up the standard MUI settings window.

     @{b}About@{ub}
       This will show some info about the program.

     @{b}OnyxSoft@{ub}
       This will show some info about OnyxSoft as this is an
       OnyxSoft product.

     @{b}Quit@{ub}
       This will just quit AmigaAMP-Prefs without saving the settings.


@endnode

